ip Stockton and Alan Spence, \"The use of Process Simulation Models in Hydrocarbon Allocation Systems\" Paper presented at 24th North Sea Flow Measurement Workshop (2006)</ref>\n*<ref name=\"savidge792\">based on Savidge (2007). \"Allocation Measurement\" p. 792</ref>\n*<ref name=\"suri\">\n{{Citation\n |last       = Suri\n |first      = S. K.\n |year       = 1995\n |title      = Liquid flow provers (conventional)\n |publisher  = Univ. of Oklahoma\n |location   = Oklahoma City\n |pages      = 435\u2013443\n |url        = https://www.etde.org/etdeweb/details.jsp?&query_id=1&page=0&osti_id=146321&printerfriendly=true\n |archive-url = https://archive.today/20130624222201/https://www.etde.org/etdeweb/details.jsp?&query_id=1&page=0&osti_id=146321&printerfriendly=true\n |url-status=dead\n |archive-date = 2013-06-24\n |accessdate = 2013-06-23\n}}\n</ref>\n*<ref name=\"Yoder\">{{Cite web\n| title = Flow Control: Custody Transfer Metering of Oil & Gas \n| accessdate = 2013-06-23\n| author = Jesse Yoder\n| url = http://www.flowcontrolnetwork.com/articles/89619-custody-transfer-metering-of-oil-gas\n}}</ref> \n<!-- This introduces a brief and clear description of the conventional well test practices to estimate individual well flow performance to solve the allocation problem: -->\n*<ref name=\"Lorentzen\">{{Cite conference\n| publisher = Society of Petroleum Engineers\n| doi = 10.2118/136026-MS\n| isbn = 9781555633134\n| last = Lorentzen\n| first = Rolf\n|author2=Ove S\u00e6vareid |author3=Geir N\u00e6vdal\n | title = Soft Multiphase Flow Metering for Accurate Production Allocation\n| accessdate = 2013-06-23\n| date = October 2010\n| url = http://www.onepetro.org/mslib/servlet/onepetropreview?id=SPE-136026-MS\n}}</ref>\n* <ref name=\"Lorentzen14Estimation\">{{Cite journal\n| pages = 172\u2013180\n| authors = Rolf J. Lorentzen, Andreas S. Stordal, Geir N\u00e6vdal, Hans A. Karlsen and Hans J. Skaug \n| title = Estimation of Production Rates With Transient Well-Flow Modeling and 