{"title_page": "Amanda Rodr\u00edguez", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Amanda Rodr\u00edguez\n| image          = \n| caption        =\n| fullname       = Amanda Rodr\u00edguez Ramos<ref name=SW>{{Soccerway|110299|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1994|11|4|df=y}}<ref name=SW/>\n| birth_place    = \n| height         = \n| position       = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]<ref name=SW/>\n| currentclub    = \n| clubnumber     = \n| youthyears1    = \n| youthclubs1    = \n| collegeyears1  = \n| college1       = \n| collegecaps1   =  \n| collegegoals1  = \n| years1 =\n| clubs1 = \n| caps1  =\n| goals1 =\n| nationalyears1 = 2009\n| nationalteam1  = {{Nwftu|17|Dominican Republic}}\n| nationalcaps1  = 2\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2011\u20132012\n| nationalteam2  = {{Nwftu|20|Dominican Republic}}\n| nationalcaps2  = 6\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3 = 2014\n| nationalteam3  = [[Dominican Republic women's national football team|Dominican Republic]]\n| nationalcaps3  = 1\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| pcupdate = \n| ntupdate = 18 November 2014\n}}\n{{Spanish name|Rodr\u00edguez|Ramos}}\n'''Amanda Rodr\u00edguez Ramos''' (born 4 November 1994) is a Dominican [[Women's association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]]. She has been a member of the [[Dominican Republic women's national football team|Dominican Republic women's national team]].\n\n==Early life==\nRodr\u00edguez hails from [[El Seibo Province]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://listindiario.com/el-deporte/2012/01/06/217174/seleccion-de-futbol-rd-busca-avanzar-a-finales|title=Selecci\u00f3n de f\u00fatbol RD busca avanzar a finales|website=List\u00edn Diario|accessdate=27 March 2020|date=6 January 2012|language=es}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nRodr\u00edguez represented the Dominican Republic at the 2010 CONCACAF Women's U-17 Championship qualifying stage and the [[2012 CONCACAF Women's U-20 Championship qualifying]].<ref name=SW/> At senior level, she capped during the [[Football at the 2014 Central American and Caribbean Games|2014 Central American and Caribbean Games]].<ref name=SW/>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rodriguez, Amanda}}\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Women's association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Dominican Republic women's footballers]]\n[[Category:People from El Seibo Province]]\n[[Category:Dominican Republic women's international footballers]]\n[[Category:Competitors at the 2014 Central American and Caribbean Games]]\n\n\n{{DominicanRepublic-footy-bio-stub}}\n{{Caribbean-women-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Amanda Rodr\u00edguez\n| image          = \n| caption        =\n| fullname       = Amanda Rodr\u00edguez Ramos<ref name=SW>{{Soccerway|110299|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1994|11|4|df=y}}<ref name=SW/>\n| birth_place    = \n| height         = \n| position       = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]<ref name=SW/>\n| currentclub    = \n| clubnumber     = \n| youthyears1    = \n| youthclubs1    = \n| collegeyears1  = \n| college1       = \n| collegecaps1   =  \n| collegegoals1  = \n| years1 =\n| clubs1 = \n| caps1  =\n| goals1 =\n| nationalyears1 = 2009\n| nationalteam1  = {{Nwftu|17|Dominican Republic}}\n| nationalcaps1  = 2\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2011\u20132012\n| nationalteam2  = {{Nwftu|20|Dominican Republic}}\n| nationalcaps2  = 6\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3 = 2014\n| nationalteam3  = [[Dominican Republic women's national football team|Dominican Republic]]\n| nationalcaps3  = 1\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| pcupdate = \n| ntupdate = 18 November 2014\n}}\n{{Spanish name|Rodr\u00edguez|Ramos}}\n'''Amanda Rodr\u00edguez Ramos''' (born 4 November 1994) is a Dominican [[Women's association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]]. She has been a member of the [[Dominican Republic women's national football team|Dominican Republic women's national team]].\n\n==Early life==\nRodr\u00edguez hails from [[El Seibo Province]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://listindiario.com/el-deporte/2012/01/06/217174/seleccion-de-futbol-rd-busca-avanzar-a-finales|title=Selecci\u00f3n de f\u00fatbol RD busca avanzar a finales|website=List\u00edn Diario|accessdate=27 March 2020|date=6 January 2012|language=es}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nRodr\u00edguez represented the Dominican Republic at the 2010 CONCACAF Women's U-17 Championship qualifying stage and the [[2012 CONCACAF Women's U-20 Championship qualifying]].<ref name=SW/> At senior level, she capped during the [[Football at the 2014 Central American and Caribbean Games|2014 Central American and Caribbean Games]].<ref name=SW/>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rodriguez, Amanda}}\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Women's association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Dominican Republic women's footballers]]\n[[Category:People from El Seibo Province]]\n[[Category:Dominican Republic women's international footballers]]\n[[Category:Competitors at the 2014 Central American and Caribbean Games]]\n", "name_user": "Joeykai", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amanda_Rodr%C3%ADguez"}
{"title_page": "WestJet Encore", "text_new": "{{for|the airline formerly called WestJet Express|Allegiant Air}}\n{{short description|Canadian regional airline owned by WestJet Airlines, Ltd.}}\n{{featured article}}\n{{Use Canadian English|date=December 2017}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2018}}\n{{Infobox airline\n|airline = WestJet Encore\n|logo = WestJetLogoOctober2018.svg\n|logo_size = 250\n| image2 = WestJet Encore - Dash 8-400 C-GWEU (Quintin Soloviev).jpg\n| caption2 = A [[Bombardier Q400]] at [[Yellowknife Airport]]\n| image2-width = 250px\n|IATA = WR\n|ICAO = WEN\n|callsign = ENCORE\n|parent = [[WestJet|WestJet Airlines, Ltd.]]\n|founded = {{start date|2013|6|24}}\n|aoc = Canada 17093,<ref>{{TCAOC|2019-08-28|179-03|Westjet+Encore}}</ref> United States 5WJF451F<ref name=\"FAA\">{{Cite web|url=https://av-info.faa.gov/detail.asp?DSGN_CODE=5WJF&OPER_FAR=129&OPER_NAME=WESTJET+ENCORE|title=Federal Aviation Administration - Airline Certificate Information - Detail View|website=av-info.faa.gov|access-date=2019-06-27}}</ref>\n|key_people= Charles Duncan (President, WestJet Encore and Executive Vice President, WestJet Airlines, Ltd.)\n|headquarters = [[Calgary]], [[Alberta]], Canada\n|hubs =\n<div>\n*[[Calgary International Airport|Calgary]]\n*{{nowrap|[[Toronto Pearson International Airport|Toronto\u2013Pearson]]}}\n</div>\n| focus_cities=\n<div>\n*[[Edmonton International Airport|Edmonton]]\n*[[Halifax Stanfield International Airport|Halifax]]\n*[[Vancouver International Airport|Vancouver]]\n</div>|\n|frequent_flyer = WestJet Rewards\n|lounge = \n|alliance = \n|fleet_size = 47<ref name=\"TCFleet\">{{TCregister|WESTJET+ENCORE|Westjet Encore|2018-06-18}}</ref>\n|destinations = 37\n\n|website = [http://www.westjet.com/encore WestJet.com]\n|image=|num_employees=}}\n'''WestJet Encore''' is a Canadian [[regional airline]] that began operations in 2013. It is owned by WestJet Airlines, Ltd. which also is the holding company for [[WestJet Airlines]]. The airline is headquartered in [[Calgary]], [[Alberta]]. In response to internal market studies about future growth limitations by WestJet Airlines operating only [[Boeing 737]] aircraft, WestJet Encore was formed to allow increased frequency of flights by using smaller aircraft, as well as to expand service to routes with less traffic.\n\nThe airline operates [[Bombardier Q400]] NextGen aircraft, a variant of the Bombardier Dash 8. The airline is the fourth largest operator of the [[Bombardier Aerospace|Bombardier]] Q400 series. Pilot bases are in Calgary and [[Toronto]], where many WestJet Encore flights operate. Air service originally started in Western Canada, but routes in the eastern half of the country were added later.\n\nThe airline is a [[low-cost carrier]]. It was initially staffed with non-union employees but the pilots have since unionized. Food is available for purchase. WestJet Encore participates in the WestJet Rewards, a revenue-based frequent flyer program that offers flight discount rewards.\n\n==History==\n===Market conditions leading to the formation of WestJet Encore (2005\u20132013)===\n\nPrior to the formation of WestJet Encore, WestJet Airlines, Inc. internal studies concluded in 2005, when the company had 50 [[Boeing 737]] aircraft, that WestJet would saturate the Canadian commercial airline market when it reached a 90\u2013100 Boeing 737 aircraft fleet. WestJet Airlines had become the second largest airline in Canada in 2002.<ref name=\"2nd largest airline in Canada\">{{cite book|last1=DeWil|first1=Bob|last2=Meyer|first2=Ron|title=Strategy: Process, Content, Context|publisher=Cengage Learning EMEA|isbn=1408019027|page=439}}</ref> Solutions included slowing expansion of the airline or adding smaller aircraft models to serve routes with less traffic. The absence of [[turboprop]] aircraft in the WestJet fleet was seen as a disadvantage compared to competitor [[Air Canada]]. In some cases where Air Canada had smaller aircraft, WestJet either avoided the market or had only one daily flight using a Boeing 737, an aircraft much larger than the ones Air Canada used.<ref name=\"AviationWeekSumers\">{{cite news|last1=Sumers|first1=Brian|title=WestJet Airlines Looks to Expand into Long-Haul|url=http://aviationweek.com/commercial-aviation/westjet-airlines-looks-expand-long-haul|accessdate=18 March 2018|work=Aviation Week and Space Technology}}</ref> Having more flights on a route than a competitor is a competitive advantage.<ref name=\"more flights is an advantage\">{{cite book|last1=Wensveen|first1=John|title=Air Transportation: A Management Advantage|date=2012|publisher=Ashgate Publishing, Ltd.|isbn=1409486826|page=204}}</ref><ref name=\"Global Airline Industry\">{{cite book|last1=Belobaba|first1=Peter|last2=Odoni|first2=Amedeo|last3=Barnhart|first3=Cynthia|title=The Global Airline Industry|date=April 1, 2009|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|isbn=0470744723|page=174|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BRtDl0CJpQIC|accessdate=20 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Westjet Encore Dash-8 Q400.jpg|thumb|alt=WestJet Encore Q400 aircraft with propellers taxiing at an airport|WestJet Encore Bombardier Q400 NextGen displaying 2013\u20132015 livery]]\nWestJet made an initial order of 20 Bombardier Dash 8-Q400 NextGen (Q400 NextGen) aircraft through a letter of intent on May 1, 2012, which resulted in a conditional order on June 28, 2012. A firm order of 20 Q400 NextGen and 25 options was announced on August 1, 2012.<ref name=\"BombardierOrder45\">{{cite web|title=WestJet Order for Up to 45 Bombardier Q400 NextGen Aircraft Goes Firm|url=https://www.bombardier.com/en/media/newsList/details.37897-westjet-order-for-up-to-45-bombardier-q400-nextgen-aircraft-goes-firm.bombardiercom.html?|publisher=Bombardier|accessdate=February 4, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209182326/https://www.bombardier.com/en/media/newsList/details.37897-westjet-order-for-up-to-45-bombardier-q400-nextgen-aircraft-goes-firm.bombardiercom.html|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"20 Q400 orders plus 25 options\">{{cite news|last1=Blachly|first1=Linda|title=WestJet firms five more Bombardier Q400 options|url=http://atwonline.com/airframes/westjet-firms-five-more-bombardier-q400-options|accessdate=February 16, 2018|work=Air Transport World|date=July 29, 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180216205907/http://atwonline.com/airframes/westjet-firms-five-more-bombardier-q400-options|archivedate=February 16, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The [[ATR-72|ATR-72-600]] had been considered,<ref>{{cite news|title=WestJet picks Bombardier planes for regional carrier|url=http://ca.reuters.com/article/businessNews/idCABRE84010920120501|accessdate=May 1, 2012|date=May 1, 2012|publisher=Reuters|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120505003813/http://ca.reuters.com/article/businessNews/idCABRE84010920120501|archivedate=May 5, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref> having a lower initial acquisition price and better fuel economy on short flights but slower speed, worse fuel economy on longer flights and slightly less passenger capacity.<ref name=\"GlobeandMailATR72\">{{cite web|title=Bombardier's Q400 faces dogfight for WestJet fleet order|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/report-on-business/bombardiers-q400-faces-dogfight-for-westjet-fleet-order/article4106778/|work=The Globe and Mail|accessdate=February 4, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170129222454/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/report-on-business/bombardiers-q400-faces-dogfight-for-westjet-fleet-order/article4106778/|archivedate=January 29, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"FinancialPostQ400selected\">{{cite web|title=WestJet chooses Bombardier Q400 for regional fleet as earnings soar|url=http://business.financialpost.com/investing/westjet-choses-bombardier-for-regional-fleet-as-earnings-soar|website=Financial Post|accessdate=February 4, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209212159/http://business.financialpost.com/investing/westjet-choses-bombardier-for-regional-fleet-as-earnings-soar|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Inauguration of air service and operating conditions===\n\nThe parent company, WestJet Airlines, Ltd., formed WestJet Encore, a low-cost carrier that is a wholly owned but legally separate airline from WestJet.<ref name=\"Encore is a LCC\">{{cite news|title=Low-cost doesn't necessarily mean best value!|url=http://www.iamaw.ca/low-cost-doesnt-necessarily-mean-best-value/|accessdate=February 10, 2018|publisher=International Association of Machinist and Aerospace Workers|date=April 25, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180211131238/http://www.iamaw.ca/low-cost-doesnt-necessarily-mean-best-value/|archivedate=February 11, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"CAPA profile\">{{cite web|title=WestJet Encore Airline Profile|url=https://centreforaviation.com/data/profiles/airlines/westjet-encore-wr|publisher=CAPA Centre for Aviation|accessdate=February 4, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209122233/https://centreforaviation.com/data/profiles/airlines/westjet-encore-wr|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"WR separate company but pilot track\">{{cite news|last1=Watson|first1=Gary|title=Two companies, one culture|url=https://www.skiesmag.com/news/18312-two-companies-one-culture-html/|accessdate=February 16, 2018|publisher=Skies|date=February 23, 2013|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180216144026/https://www.skiesmag.com/news/18312-two-companies-one-culture-html/|archivedate=February 16, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Prior to the selection of the Encore name, other names were considered, including [[Chinook wind|Chinook]], Echo, and Reach.<ref name=\"Echo Reach Chinook\">{{cite news|last1=Deveau|first1=Scott|title=WestJet trademarks potential names for regional carrier|url=http://business.financialpost.com/transportation/westjet-trademarks-potential-names-for-regional-carrier|accessdate=February 9, 2018|work=Financial Post|date=September 12, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209213705/http://business.financialpost.com/transportation/westjet-trademarks-potential-names-for-regional-carrier|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Calgary was selected for the WestJet Encore corporate headquarters but Toronto Pearson International Airport was also considered.<ref name=\"YYZ rejected as HQ\">{{cite news|last1=Osbourn|first1=Erin|title=WestJet passes on Pearson, makes Calgary new regional HQ|url=https://www.mississauga.com/news-story/4242402-westjet-passes-on-pearson-makes-calgary-new-regional-hq/|accessdate=February 10, 2018|work=Mississauga News|date=October 31, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180211072205/https://www.mississauga.com/news-story/4242402-westjet-passes-on-pearson-makes-calgary-new-regional-hq/|archivedate=February 11, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> WestJet Encore received an Air Operator Certificate separate from WestJet Airlines on June 12, 2013.<ref name=\"WR AOC\">{{cite web|title=WestJet Encore receives its Air Operator Certificate|url=https://worldairlinenews.com/2013/06/12/westjet-encore-receives-its-air-operator-certificate/|website=World Airline News|accessdate=February 3, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180129141030/https://worldairlinenews.com/2013/06/12/westjet-encore-receives-its-air-operator-certificate/|archivedate=January 29, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"ATW AOC\">{{cite web|last1=Karp|first1=Aaron|title=WestJet Encore receives AOC from Transport Canada|url=http://atwonline.com/finance-amp-data/westjet-encore-receives-aoc-transport-canada|website=Air Transport World|accessdate=February 4, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209125226/http://atwonline.com/finance-amp-data/westjet-encore-receives-aoc-transport-canada|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn June 24, 2013, with two Q400s in its fleet, it began flights.<ref name=\"AirlineReporterInguralFlt\">{{cite web|last1=Slutsken|first1=Howard|title=WestJet Encore Celebrates Inaugural Q400 Flight from Calgary|url=https://www.airlinereporter.com/2013/06/westjet-encore-launch-day/|website=Airline Reporter|accessdate=February 4, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170702085317/http://www.airlinereporter.com/2013/06/westjet-encore-launch-day/|archivedate=July 2, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> That day, the airline flew between [[Calgary International Airport]] and [[Saskatoon John G. Diefenbaker International Airport|Saskatoon]], [[Nanaimo Airport|Nanaimo (British Columbia)]], and [[Fort St. John Airport|Fort St. John (British Columbia)]] as well as between Fort. St. John and [[Vancouver International Airport|Vancouver]].<ref name=\"Encore starts\">{{cite web|title=WestJet Encore celebrates three years: WestJet's regional airline now at 32 destinations and 30 aircraft|url=https://www.newswire.ca/news-releases/westjet-encore-celebrates-three-years-584242681.html|publisher=Cision|accessdate=January 30, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210002159/https://www.newswire.ca/news-releases/westjet-encore-celebrates-three-years-584242681.html|archivedate=February 10, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The IATA assigned WestJet Encore an airline code of \"WR\",<ref name=\"EncoreisWR\">{{cite web|title=WestJet Encore C-GWEN|url=http://www.airfleets.net/ficheapp/plane-dh8-4537.htm|publisher=Airfleets.net|accessdate=February 5, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209182341/http://www.airfleets.net/ficheapp/plane-dh8-4537.htm|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> which had previously been used by [[Royal Tongan Airlines]].<ref name=\"Royal Tongan\">{{cite web|last1=van Noordenne|first1=Marcel|title=Royal Tongan Airlines|url=http://www.b757.info/royal-tongan-airlines/|publisher=MNVS Boeing 757|accessdate=February 5, 2018|ref=December 7, 2014}}</ref>\n\nSome WestJet Encore flights were new routes not served by the WestJet mainline carrier because there was insufficient traffic to support Boeing 737 flights. Other WestJet Encore flights increased frequencies on existing WestJet routes.<ref name=AviationWeekSumers /> WestJet Encore's service was initially limited to Western Canada, but it opened service in the eastern part of the country<!--not Eastern Canada, as NB is Eastern Canada, not Toronto--> in June 2014 with a route from Toronto to Thunder Bay, Ontario.<ref name=\"WRexpandsEast\">{{cite web|last1=Stephenson|first1=Amanda|title=WestJet Encore begins march east|url=https://calgaryherald.com/business/westjet+encore+begins+march+east/9974530/story.html| work=Calgary Herald|accessdate=February 5, 2018|ref=June 25, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140715051140/http://www.calgaryherald.com/business/WestJet+Encore+begins+march+east/9974530/story.html |archivedate=July 15, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref> It later began service on eastern routes centred on Toronto and Halifax.<ref name = \"WRexpandsEast\" /> WestJet Encore moved into the international market in 2016, with flights serving [[Boston Logan Airport]];<ref name=\"BOS service\">{{cite web|title=WestJet Encore inaugurates service to Boston|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/westjet-encore-inaugurates-service-to-boston-572079671.html|publisher=Cision|accessdate=February 5, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210002146/https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/westjet-encore-inaugurates-service-to-boston-572079671.html|archivedate=February 10, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Boston first Intl\">{{cite news|last1=Lu|first1=Vanessa|title=WestJet to launch regional Toronto-Boston service|url=https://www.thestar.com/business/2015/07/20/westjet-to-launch-regional-toronto-boston-service.html|accessdate=February 16, 2018|work=Toronto Star|date=July 20, 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180216143959/https://www.thestar.com/business/2015/07/20/westjet-to-launch-regional-toronto-boston-service.html|archivedate=February 16, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> [[Nashville International Airport]] was added the following year.<ref name=\"BNA service\">{{cite web|title=WestJet Launches Calgary's First Nonstop to Nashville|url=http://press.tnvacation.com/news-archive/westjet-launches-calgarys-first-nonstop-nashville|publisher=Tennessee Department of Tourist Development|accessdate=February 5, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210002141/http://press.tnvacation.com/news-archive/westjet-launches-calgarys-first-nonstop-nashville|archivedate=February 10, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[File:WestJetQ400C-GEWRUnloadingYYJAugust2018.jpg|thumb|left|A WestJet Encore Bombardier Q400 displaying the new livery]]\nWestJet Encore flies Q400 NextGen on regional flights up to 700 nautical miles.<ref name=\"Q400 700nmi flights\">{{cite web|title=Flight Review of WestJet Encore: On Board Their Newest Q400|url=https://www.wingborn.com/flight-review-of-westjet-encore-on-board-their-newest-q400/|publisher=Wingborn|accessdate=February 5, 2018|ref=October 25, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209183808/https://www.wingborn.com/flight-review-of-westjet-encore-on-board-their-newest-q400/|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> 50% of WestJet Encore passengers are traveling on connecting flights with WestJet.<ref name=\"WRexpandsEast\" /><ref name=\"YYC ltd flexible gates\"/> The WestJet Encore fleet of Q400s expanded to 18 aircraft by March 2015, and later to 34 aircraft by December 2016 and to 43 aircraft by December 2017.<ref name=AviationWeekSumers/><ref name=\"Utah Herald 34 Q400s\">{{cite news|last1=Roges|first1=Linda|title=ProPetro Holding Corp. (PUMP Reaches $17.65 After 6.00% Down Move; Westjet Airlines Ltd (WJAFF) Shorts Decreased By 17.24%|url=https://utahherald.com/propetro-holding-corp-pump-reaches-17-65-after-6-00-down-move-westjet-airlines-ltd-wjaff-shorts-decreased-by-17-24/|accessdate=February 5, 2018|work=Utah Herald|date=February 4, 2018}}{{Dead link|date=August 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> In 2015, WestJet Encore was the fastest-growing operator of Q400 aircraft.<ref name=\"Encore starts\" /> By 2017, it was the fourth largest operator of Q400 aircraft in the world.<ref name=\"WR YUL BOS 4th largest Q400\">{{cite news|last1=Simpson|first1=Brian|title=WestJet Launches Montreal-Boston Service|url=https://ca.travelpulse.com/news/airlines/westjet-launches-montreal-boston-service.html|accessdate=February 5, 2018|publisher=Travel Pulse Canada|date=October 15, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209122235/https://ca.travelpulse.com/news/airlines/westjet-launches-montreal-boston-service.html|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2015, WestJet Encore adopted a revised livery. The tail and type style used with the word \"WestJet\" remained the same, but the teal-and-blue geometric widget ahead of the WestJet titles was replaced with a teal-and-blue stylized maple leaf with a similar pattern.<ref name=\"revised livery\">{{cite news|title=WestJet Gets a New Logo&nbsp;\u2013 Really!|url=http://www.wingborn.com/westjet-gets-a-new-logo-really/|accessdate=February 8, 2018|publisher=Wingborn/Airline Reporter|date=August 27, 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209183813/http://www.wingborn.com/westjet-gets-a-new-logo-really/|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Q400 new livery\">{{cite web|last1=Flynn|first1=Shawn|title=WestJet Encore de Havilland Canada DHC-8-400Q / Bombardier Q400 C-GKWE|url=https://www.airplane-pictures.net/photo/903207/c-gkwe-westjet-encore-de-havilland-canada-dhc-8-400q-bombardier-q400/|publisher=Airplane Pictures|accessdate=February 8, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210002131/https://www.airplane-pictures.net/photo/903207/c-gkwe-westjet-encore-de-havilland-canada-dhc-8-400q-bombardier-q400/|archivedate=February 10, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[File:WestJet Encore - Bombardier Dash 8 Q400 (Quintin Soloviev).png|thumb|WestJet Encore Bombardier Dash 8-Q400 at Qu\u00e9bec City Jean Lesage International Airport.]]\n\nWestjet Encore has a partially unionized workforce. Initially having an entirely non-union staff, the airline became a target for union drives starting in 2014.<ref name = \"WestJet Encore pilots unionize\">{{cite news|title=WestJet Encore pilots unionize and flight attendants could be next|url=https://ca.finance.yahoo.com/news/westjet-encore-pilots-unionize-flight-194612798.html|accessdate=February 6, 2018|publisher=Yahoo Finance Canada|date=November 1, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209122406/https://ca.finance.yahoo.com/news/westjet-encore-pilots-unionize-flight-194612798.html|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Starting January 1, 2016, the airline management initiated WestJet Pilots Association, a subgroup of the WestJet Proactive Management Team, to ratify pilot contracts between with WestJet Encore.<ref name=\"WJPA before ALPA\">{{cite news|title=WestJet Encore Pilots Ratify Deal|url=http://www.cbj.ca/westjet-encore-pilots-ratify-new-contract/|accessdate=February 6, 2018|work=Canadian Business Journal|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210002228/http://www.cbj.ca/westjet-encore-pilots-ratify-new-contract/|archivedate=February 10, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The pilots union which represents many pilots that fly for U.S. carriers,<ref name=\"ALPA 59000 pilots in US Canada\">{{cite web|title=What We Do&nbsp;\u2013 ALPA|url=http://www.alpa.org/en/about-alpa/what-we-do|publisher=Air Line Pilots Association|accessdate=February 6, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170606122948/http://www.alpa.org/en/about-alpa/what-we-do|archivedate=June 6, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> the [[Air Line Pilots Association]], was successful in unionizing the 500-pilot workforce in November 2017.<ref name=\"500 pilots join ALPA union\">{{cite news|title=WestJet's 500 Encore pilots officially join union; company 'disappointed'|url=https://calgaryherald.com/business/local-business/westjets-500-encore-pilots-officially-join-union-company-disappointed|accessdate=February 6, 2018|work=Calgary Herald|date=November 30, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201025411/http://calgaryherald.com/business/local-business/westjets-500-encore-pilots-officially-join-union-company-disappointed|archivedate=December 1, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Pilot bases are located in Calgary and Toronto. WestJet pilots are required to be Canadian citizens or Canadian permanent residents.<ref name=\"PilotCareerCentre\">{{cite web|title=WestJet Encore|url=https://www.pilotcareercentre.com/Air-Carrier-PCC-Profile/3363/WestJet-Encore|publisher=Pilot Career Centre Global|accessdate=February 4, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209182321/https://www.pilotcareercentre.com/Air-Carrier-PCC-Profile/3363/WestJet-Encore|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Pilot shortages in the airline industry have affected WestJet Encore, resulting in requirements that newly hired pilots need only 1,000 flight hours of experience prior to hiring.<ref name=\"pilot shortage\">{{cite news|last1=Donnelly|first1=Sara|title=Pilot shortage affects airline|url=http://www.prpeak.com/business/pilot-shortage-affects-airline-1.23153044|accessdate=February 1, 2018|work=Powell River Peak|date=January 24, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180124220316/http://www.prpeak.com/business/pilot-shortage-affects-airline-1.23153044|archivedate=January 24, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Pilots are guaranteed an eventual higher paying position flying larger jets at WestJet, unlike competitor airline [[Jazz (airline)|Jazz]], which does not offer guarantees of an eventual job at Air Canada.<ref name=\"WR separate company but pilot track\" /> WestJet Encore and its flight attendants reached an agreement regarding compensation and work rules beginning January 1, 2018, for a one-year period. However, the Canadian Union of Public Employees (CUPE), who was not a party to the agreement, announced that it would continue efforts to unionize the flight attendant ranks.<ref name=\"CUPE flight attendants 2018\">{{cite news|title=Union drive still on after WestJet Encore flight attendant agreement: CUPE|url=http://business.financialpost.com/pmn/business-pmn/westjet-encore-reaches-peace-with-flight-attendants-months-after-union-drive|accessdate=February 6, 2018|work=Financial Post|date=January 9, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209190302/http://business.financialpost.com/pmn/business-pmn/westjet-encore-reaches-peace-with-flight-attendants-months-after-union-drive|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn October 31, 2016, a $2 billion, two million square foot international terminal for U.S. cross border and international flights opened at Calgary International Airport, the largest hub of WestJet Encore and its affiliate WestJet.<ref name=\"Calg Herald 20Dec16 YYC walk baggage 2M sq ft\">{{cite news|last1=Stephenson|first1=Amanda|title=WestJet CEO blasts new terminal at YYC, says airport authority hasn't listened to concerns|url=https://calgaryherald.com/business/local-business/westjet-ceo-blasts-new-terminal-at-yyc-says-airport-authority-hasnt-listened-to-concerns|accessdate=February 6, 2018|work=Calgary Herald|date=December 20, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170708164910/http://calgaryherald.com/business/local-business/westjet-ceo-blasts-new-terminal-at-yyc-says-airport-authority-hasnt-listened-to-concerns|archivedate=July 8, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"YYC largest hub\">{{cite news|last1=Rumbolt|first1=Ryan|title=WestJet adds dozens of Calgary departures as economy shows signs of recovery|url=https://calgaryherald.com/news/local-news/westjet-adds-dozens-of-calgary-departures-as-economy-shows-signs-of-recovery|accessdate=14 March 2018|work=Calgary Herald|date=January 29, 2018}}</ref> Despite consultation with the airlines, the terminal design proved problematic.<ref name=\"Airlines consulted for YYC\">{{cite news|last1=Tighe|first1=Tony|title=WestJet says passengers upset with Calgary airport connection travel times|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/3142232/westjet-says-passengers-upset-with-calgary-airport-connection-travel-times/|accessdate=14 March 2018|publisher=Global News|date=December 31, 2016}}</ref> The Calgary Airport Authority CEO characterized the new terminal as being \"long on aesthetics and short on functionality.\"<ref name=\"YYC CEO on Intl Term\">{{cite news|last1=Yedlin|first1=Deborah|title=Yedlin: New CEO determined to fix international terminal troubles at YYC|url=https://calgaryherald.com/business/local-business/yedlin-new-ceo-determined-to-fix-international-terminal-troubles-at-yyc|accessdate=February 6, 2018|work=Calgary Herald|date=February 28, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170609141047/http://calgaryherald.com/business/local-business/yedlin-new-ceo-determined-to-fix-international-terminal-troubles-at-yyc|archivedate=June 9, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> There is reduced aircraft efficiency due to the need to tow aircraft to another concourse if an aircraft is used for both domestic and either U.S. cross border or international flights<ref name=\"YYC ltd flexible gates\">{{cite news|last1=Yedlin|first1=Deborah|title=Yedlin: New international terminal at YYC falls short of its peers|url=https://calgaryherald.com/business/energy/yedlin-new-international-terminal-at-yyc-falls-short-of-its-peers|accessdate=February 6, 2018|work=Calgary Herald|date=January 11, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170115055230/http://calgaryherald.com/business/energy/yedlin-new-international-terminal-at-yyc-falls-short-of-its-peers|archivedate=January 15, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> as well as the need to hire additional staff because they cannot be deployed to more than one concourse due to long walking distances.<ref name=\"CBC YYC terminal doesnt work\">{{cite news|last1=Bell|first1=David|title='It just doesn't work for us': WestJet on new YYC international terminal|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/calgary/westjet-yyc-terminal-complaints-1.3908218|accessdate=February 6, 2018|publisher=CBC|date=December 21, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171221090816/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/calgary/westjet-yyc-terminal-complaints-1.3908218|archivedate=December 21, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The baggage system of the new terminal is inoperable with the rest of the airport from 2016 to 2019.<ref name=\"Calg Herald 20Dec16 YYC walk baggage 2M sq ft\"/> Passenger problems include WestJet trans-border and international gates being up to a two-kilometre walk to the domestic WestJet gates as well as lack of enough seating at the gate so passengers sit on the floor.<ref name=\"Calg Herald 20Dec16 YYC walk baggage 2M sq ft\"/><ref name=\"YYC CEO on Intl Term\"/><ref name=\"CBC YYC terminal doesnt work\"/> These problems are seen as a threat to passenger traffic, which might be driven to other connecting airports, such as Seattle or Vancouver, cities that WestJet Encore has fewer or no flights serving.<ref name=\"YYC ltd flexible gates\"/>\n\n==Corporate affairs==\n===Management===\n\nWestJet Encore is a wholly owned company of WestJet Airlines, Ltd. Sales and marketing of WestJet Encore flights are conducted by WestJet, An Alberta Partnership, which is jointly owned by two corporate entities owned by WestJet Airlines, Ltd.<ref name=\"2016 annual report\">{{cite web|last1=WestJet Airlines, Ltd.|title=2016 Annual Information Form|url=https://www.westjet.com/assets/wj-web/documents/en/about-us/financialReports/WestJet2016AIF.pdf|publisher=WestJet|accessdate=14 March 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe first president of WestJet Encore was Ferio Pugliese, who retained his title of Executive Vice President at WestJet Airlines, Ltd. He was hired in November 2012 coming from WestJet, where he began work in 2007.<ref name=\"Puegliese hired\">{{cite web|title=WestJet appoints President, WestJet Encore|url=http://westjet2.mediaroom.com/index.php?item=719&s=43|publisher=WestJet|accessdate=February 8, 2018}}</ref> He left<ref name=\"Bloomberg about Ferio\">{{cite web|title=Ferio Pugliese|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/profiles/people/7339778-ferio-pugliese|publisher=Bloomberg|accessdate=6 April 2018}}</ref> in 2016 to become an Executive Vice President at [[Hydro One|Hydro One Ltd.]], an electricity company.<ref name=\"Pugliese Hydro One\">{{cite news|title=westjet airlines ltd (WJAFF:OTC US)|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=25985084&privcapId=883197|accessdate=February 8, 2018|publisher=Bloomberg}}</ref> He was replaced in September 2016 by Charles Duncan, an American who previously worked as Senior Vice President of Technical Operations at [[United Airlines]] and, earlier in his career, was Chief Operating Officer at [[Continental Micronesia]].<ref name=\"Charles Duncan President\">{{cite web|title=WestJet announces new president for WestJet Encore|url=https://www.newswire.ca/news-releases/westjet-announces-new-president-for-westjet-encore-624644754.html|publisher=Cision|accessdate=February 8, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170611075237/http://www.newswire.ca/news-releases/westjet-announces-new-president-for-westjet-encore-624644754.html|archivedate=June 11, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Financials===\n\nFinancial statistics are not released separately for WestJet Encore but reported for WestJet Airlines, Ltd., which comprises several units and the larger WestJet Airlines.<ref name=\"Annual report\">{{cite web|title=2016 Annual Report|url=https://www.westjet.com/assets/wj-web/documents/en/about-us/financialReports/WestJet2016AR.pdf|publisher=WestJet|accessdate=February 9, 2018}}</ref> WestJet Encore has increased traffic in markets that it served as well as lowered airfares 30\u201340% than was previously available.<ref name=\"WR increase traffic lowers fares\">{{cite news|title=WestJet after 20 years. The new LCC challenges: preserving the culture but rising to the business|url=https://centreforaviation.com/insights/analysis/westjet-turns-20-the-new-lcc-challenges-preserving-the-culture-but-rising-to-the-business-280095|accessdate=February 10, 2018|publisher=CAPA Centre for Aviation|date=May 9, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180211131158/https://centreforaviation.com/insights/analysis/westjet-turns-20-the-new-lcc-challenges-preserving-the-culture-but-rising-to-the-business-280095|archivedate=February 11, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Destinations==\n{{Further|List of WestJet destinations}}\n{{Location map+ | Canada\n| AlternativeMap = Relief map of Canada.png\n| width   = 250\n| caption = Airports served by scheduled WestJet Encore flights in January 2018 (two additional United States airports not shown, Nashville and Myrtle Beach)\n| places  =\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 45.42\n  | lon_deg = -75.7\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 49.25\n  | lon_deg = -123.1\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 51\n  | lon_deg = -114\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 53.5\n  | lon_deg = -113.5\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 56.7\n  | lon_deg = -111.3\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 55.2\n  | lon_deg = -118.7\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 49\n  | lon_deg = -122.3\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 49.7\n  | lon_deg = -124.9\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 56.2\n  | lon_deg = -120.85\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 50.6\n  | lon_deg = -120.3\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 49.9\n  | lon_deg = -119.5\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 49.15\n  | lon_deg = -123.9\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 49.5\n  | lon_deg = -119.6\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 53.9\n  | lon_deg = -122.74\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 54.5\n  | lon_deg = -128.6\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 48.4\n  | lon_deg = -123.35\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 49.9\n  | lon_deg = -99.95\n  | label   = \n  }}\n <!-- {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 36.2\n  | lon_deg = -86.8\n  | label   = \n  }} -->\n<!--  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 33.75\n  | lon_deg = -78.9\n  | label   = \n  }} -->\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 49.9\n  | lon_deg = -97.1\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 45.95\n  | lon_deg = -66.66\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 46.1\n  | lon_deg = -64.8\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 47.6\n  | lon_deg = -52.7\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 48.9\n  | lon_deg = -54.5\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 49.2\n  | lon_deg = -57.4\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 46.1\n  | lon_deg = -61.0\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 44.9\n  | lon_deg = -63.5\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 62.5\n  | lon_deg = -114.4\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 45.5\n  | lon_deg = -73.7\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 46.8\n  | lon_deg = -71.4\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 52.2\n  | lon_deg = -106.7\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 50.4\n  | lon_deg = -104.65\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 46.6\n  | lon_deg = -80.8\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 48.3\n  | lon_deg = -89.3\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 43.65\n  | lon_deg = -79.6\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 43\n  | lon_deg = -81.15\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 42.35\n  | lon_deg = -71\n  | label   = \n  }}\n}}\n\nWestJet Encore flies regional routes throughout Canada, primarily to or from Calgary, Toronto, and Halifax. Routes include smaller cities, such as [[Brandon, Manitoba]] to Calgary, two cities with an oil industry. This new service re-introduced air service to Brandon.<ref name=\"Brandon and oil industry\">{{cite news|last1=Forlanski|first1=Tamara|title=WestJet lands in Brandon with service to Calgary|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/557244/brandon-gets-westjet-service-starting-sept-3/|accessdate=February 9, 2018|publisher=Global News|date=May 13, 2013|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209122844/https://globalnews.ca/news/557244/brandon-gets-westjet-service-starting-sept-3/|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Other routes are increased frequencies on existing WestJet routes, such as between Calgary and Saskatoon.<ref name=\"Saskatoon schedule\">{{cite news|last1=Streck|first1=Aaron|title=WestJet Encore touches down in Saskatoon|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/671271/westjet-encore-touches-down-in-saskatoon/|accessdate=February 9, 2018|publisher=Global News|date=June 25, 2013|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209122839/https://globalnews.ca/news/671271/westjet-encore-touches-down-in-saskatoon/|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> WestJet Encore services four destinations outside of Canada, namely Boston, Nashville, Portland, OR and on a seasonal basis, [[Myrtle Beach International Airport|Myrtle Beach, South Carolina]].<ref name=\"MYR SC\">{{cite news|last1=McGee|first1=Kendell|title=Airlines announce more direct flights, lower fares in and out of MYR|url=http://www.wbtw.com/news/airlines-announce-more-direct-flights-lower-fares-in-and-out-of-myr/868551671|accessdate=10 April 2018|publisher=WBTV|date=January 19, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"BOS service and BNA\">{{cite web|title=WestJet Encore inaugurates service to Boston|url=https://www.meetingscanada.com/boston-toronto-westjet-encore-service/|publisher=Meetings Canada|accessdate=February 5, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209182156/https://www.meetingscanada.com/boston-toronto-westjet-encore-service/|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> WestJet Encore operated flights between [[Kelowna International Airport|Kelowna, British Columbia]] and [[Fort McMurray International Airport|Fort McMurray, Alberta]], neither a WestJet Encore hub airport, from 2014 to 2016 but discontinued flights amid a decline in the oil industry due to lower oil prices.<ref name=\"YLW YMM service begins\">{{cite web|title=WestJet Encore launches new Fort McMurray service|url=https://ylw.kelowna.ca/news-events/news/westjet-encore-launches-new-fort-mcmurray-service|publisher=Kelowna International Airport|accessdate=8 April 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"YMM YLW service ending\">{{cite news|title=WestJet suspends Fort McMurray to Kelowna service amid oil slump|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/calgary/westjet-suspends-flights-fort-mcmurray-kelowna-1.3410240|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=CBC|date=January 19, 2016}}</ref> WestJet Encore flights are numbered as flight 3100 to 3899.<ref name=\"flights 3100 3899\">{{cite web|title=WestJet Encore|url=https://www.westjet.com/en-ca/about-us/fleet/westjet-encore|publisher=WestJet|accessdate=February 9, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210002347/https://www.westjet.com/en-ca/about-us/fleet/westjet-encore|archivedate=February 10, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Fleet==\n[[File:C-FWEP Westjet Encore Dash 8-Q400.jpg|thumb|left|alt=WestJet Encore Q400 in flight with propellers turning and landing gear extended|WestJet Encore Bombardier Q400 NextGen with landing gear extended]]\n\nWestJet Encore operates one type of aircraft, the Bombardier Q400 NextGen, an updated version of the Q400 with updated landing gear, redesigned interiors, lighting, and larger overhead cabin storage. In turn, the Q400 is an updated version of the Bombardier Dash 8-400 that has active noise suppression to create a quieter passenger cabin. To prevent freezing of water lines during overnight stays at airports with cold weather, the airline rendered the water flow to the lavatory basins inoperative in 2013.<ref name=\"WR Q400 review\">{{cite news|last1=Slutsken|first1=Howard|title=Flight Review of Westjet Encore: On Board Their Newest Q400|url=https://www.airlinereporter.com/2013/10/flight-review-of-westjet-encore-on-board-their-newest-q400/|accessdate=January 30, 2018|publisher=Airline Reporter|date=October 25, 2013|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170829081507/http://www.airlinereporter.com/2013/10/flight-review-of-westjet-encore-on-board-their-newest-q400/|archivedate=August 29, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nWestJet Encore uses a navAero supplied Windows-OS based [[electronic flight bag]] (EFB) that can connect to the aircraft. In conjunction with a WestJet developed Integrated Communication and Application System (ICAS), objective flight data can be shared with maintenance personnel improving aircraft efficiency. One example of use would be after an aircraft was subjected to severe turbulence, EFB and ICAS could determine whether or not objective thresholds were exceeded. If such thresholds are not exceeded, four hours of maintenance and inspection are avoided instead of having pilots subjectively characterize the level of turbulence.<ref name=\"MRO\">{{cite web |title=Exploiting Turboprop Data For Smarter Maintenance |url=http://www.mro-network.com/maintenance-repair-overhaul/exploiting-turboprop-data-smarter-maintenance |publisher=MRO Network |date=August 21, 2017 |accessdate=January 2, 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180103133306/http://www.mro-network.com/maintenance-repair-overhaul/exploiting-turboprop-data-smarter-maintenance |archivedate=January 3, 2018 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nAs of August 2019, the WestJet Encore fleet consists of the following aircraft:<ref>{{cite journal |title=Global Airline Guide 2019 (Part One) |journal=Airliner World |volume=October 2019 |page=9}}</ref><ref>https://www.westjet.com/en-ca/about-us/fleet/westjet-encore</ref>\n<center>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; margin:0.5em\"\n|+ WestJet Encore fleet'''\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:120px;\" |Aircraft\n! rowspan=\"2\" |In service\n! colspan=\"3\" | Passengers\n|-\n! <abbr title=\"Premium Economy\">W</abbr>\n! <abbr title=\"Economy\">Y</abbr>\n! Total\n|-\n|[[De Havilland Canada Dash 8#Series 400|Bombardier Q400]]\n|47\n|10\n|68\n|78\n|-\n|}\n</center>\n\n==Marketing==\nWestJet Encore participates in WestJet Rewards, a [[frequent flyer program]] and loyalty scheme originally started by WestJet. Instead of miles or points, WestJet Dollars are earned by participants and can be redeemed as full or partial payment of future airfare. Participants earn 1% of their airfare in WestJet Dollars. Elite level participants, who spend $3000 or more per year in WestJet airfare are classified as Silver or Gold and earn a 3% or 5% rate in WestJet Dollars.<ref name=\"WestJet Rewards Tiers\">{{cite web|title=Tiers|url=https://www.westjet.com/en-ca/rewards/tiers/index|publisher=WestJet|accessdate=February 9, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210002344/https://www.westjet.com/en-ca/rewards/tiers/index|archivedate=February 10, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> WestJet also participates in WestJet Rewards as does Air France (2017\u2013present),<ref name=\"Flying Blue\">{{cite news|title=Air France-KLM and WestJet now offer reciprocal frequent flyer benefits|url=http://www.travelweek.ca/news/air-france-klm-westjet-now-offer-reciprocal-frequent-flyer-benefits/|accessdate=February 10, 2018|publisher=Travel Week|date=August 30, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210121008/http://www.travelweek.ca/news/air-france-klm-westjet-now-offer-reciprocal-frequent-flyer-benefits/|archivedate=February 10, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> KLM (2017\u2013present),<ref name=\"Flying Blue\"/> Delta Airlines (2014\u2013present),<ref name=\"Delta Skymiles\">{{cite news|title=Delta and WestJet Start New Accrual Partnership|url=https://pro.delta.com/content/agency/mx/en/news/products---services-archive/2014/december-2014/delta-and-westjet-start-new-accrual-partnership-.html|accessdate=February 10, 2018|publisher=Delta Airlines|date=December 18, 2014}}</ref> and Qantas (2016\u2013present).<ref name=\"Qantas Frequent Flyer\">{{cite news|title=WestJet, Qantas unveil reciprocal frequent flyer agreement: expands on existing code-share relationship|url=https://www.qantasnewsroom.com.au/media-releases/westjet-qantas-unveil-reciprocal-frequent-flyer-agreement-expands-on-existing-code-share-relationship/|accessdate=February 10, 2018|publisher=Qantas Airways|date=May 26, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210235026/https://www.qantasnewsroom.com.au/media-releases/westjet-qantas-unveil-reciprocal-frequent-flyer-agreement-expands-on-existing-code-share-relationship/|archivedate=February 10, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> WestJet Dollars earned as a base amount do not expire but bonus amounts have an expiry date.<ref name=\"WS Rewards terms and conditions\">{{cite web|title=Terms and conditions \u2013 WestJet Rewards|url=https://www.westjet.com/en-ca/rewards/terms-conditions|publisher=WestJet|accessdate=February 9, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210002342/https://www.westjet.com/en-ca/rewards/terms-conditions|archivedate=February 10, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nPassengers flying on WestJet Encore may alternatively receive credit in Air France/KLM Flying Blue,<ref name=\"Flying Blue2\">{{cite web|title=Westjet|url=https://www.flyingblue.com/earn-miles/airlines/partner/288/westjet.html|publisher=Flying Blue|accessdate=February 9, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209122217/https://www.flyingblue.com/earn-miles/airlines/partner/288/westjet.html|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Flying Blue CTV News\">{{cite news|last1=Franklin|first1=Michael|title=WestJet, Air France and KLM announce frequent flyer redemption agreement|url=https://calgary.ctvnews.ca/westjet-air-france-and-klm-announce-frequent-flyer-redemption-agreement-1.3678758|accessdate=February 16, 2018|publisher=CTV Calgary|date=November 15, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180216204353/https://calgary.ctvnews.ca/westjet-air-france-and-klm-announce-frequent-flyer-redemption-agreement-1.3678758|archivedate=February 16, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Delta Skymiles,<ref name=\"Delta Skymiles2\">{{cite web|title=How to earn miles|url=https://www.delta.com/content/www/en_US/skymiles/how-to-earn-miles/airline-partners.html|publisher=Delta Airlines|accessdate=February 9, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210002239/https://www.delta.com/content/www/en_US/skymiles/how-to-earn-miles/airline-partners.html|archivedate=February 10, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> or Qantas Frequent Flyer<ref name=\"Qantas Frequent Flyer2\">{{cite web|title=Airline Partners \u2013 Westjet|url=https://www.qantas.com/fflyer/dyn/partners/airline/westjet|publisher=Qantas Airways|accessdate=February 9, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209182326/https://www.qantas.com/fflyer/dyn/partners/airline/westjet|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Cabins and services==\n[[File:WestJetEncoreQ400SeatOverviewAugust2018.webm|thumb|Seat tour of a WestJet Encore Bombardier Q400 aircraft]]\nAs well as economy class seating, WestJet Encore aircraft has a designated Plus section. Unlike the Plus section on the mainline carrier, WestJet, it does not have increased legroom. The Plus section on WestJet Encore has seating in the forward part of the cabin and does not have change fees when changing flights ticketed.<ref name=\"Plus section\">{{cite web|title=Plus Upgrade|url=https://www.westjet.com/en-ca/travel-info/check-in/options/plus-upgrade|website=WestJet|accessdate=February 10, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180211071541/https://www.westjet.com/en-ca/travel-info/check-in/options/plus-upgrade|archivedate=February 11, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The majority of WestJet Encore flights do not use [[jet bridge]]s and are instead ground loaded, meaning the passengers exit the terminal onto the [[Airport apron|apron]] before stepping on to the aircraft. WestJet Encore aircraft do not have drop down oxygen masks, which are not required by regulations due to the aircraft's certification to operate up to 25,000 feet in altitude.<ref name=\"smoke in cabin\">{{cite news|title=TSB investigators sent to B.C. airport after smoke-filled WestJet flight's emergency landing|url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/tsb-investigators-sent-to-b-c-airport-after-smoke-filled-westjet-flight-s-emergency-landing-1.3851949|accessdate=22 March 2018|publisher=CTV News}}</ref>\n\nStarting in 2014, newly hired flight attendants are required to be bilingual in English and French. As a result, 94% of flight attendants are bilingual.<ref name=\"CBC bilingual flight attendants\">{{cite news|last1=Marowitz|first1=Ross|title=WestJet takes on Air Canada on its home turf by adding service in Quebec|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/business/westjet-quebec-expansion-1.3980761|accessdate=January 30, 2018|publisher=CBC|date=February 13, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171102150710/http://www.cbc.ca/news/business/westjet-quebec-expansion-1.3980761|archivedate=November 2, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nFood is available for purchase.\n\nWestJet Encore does not operate airport lounges but has arrangements with private, non-airline affiliated airport lounges where WestJet Encore passengers are extended a discount for pay-for-visit use.<ref name=\"airport lounges\">{{cite web|title=Airport Lounges|url=https://www.westjet.com/en-ca/book-trip/business-travel/airport-lounges|publisher=WestJet|accessdate=February 10, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170815235432/https://www.westjet.com/en-ca/book-trip/business-travel/airport-lounges|archivedate=August 15, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[WestJet Link]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{commons category|WestJet Encore}}\n{{Portal bar|Canada|Companies|Aviation}}\n\n{{Airlines of Canada}}\n\n[[Category:Air Transport Association of Canada]]\n[[Category:WestJet]]\n[[Category:Low-cost carriers]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Calgary]]\n[[Category:Canadian brands]]\n[[Category:Regional airline brands]]\n[[Category:Airlines established in 2013]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the airline formerly called WestJet Express|Allegiant Air}}\n{{short description|Canadian regional airline owned by WestJet Airlines, Ltd.}}\n{{featured article}}\n{{Use Canadian English|date=December 2017}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2018}}\n{{Infobox airline\n|airline = WestJet Encore\n|logo = WestJetLogoOctober2018.svg\n|logo_size = 250\n| image2 = WestJet Encore - Dash 8-400 C-GWEU (Quintin Soloviev).jpg\n| caption2 = A [[Bombardier Q400]] at [[Yellowknife Airport]]\n| image2-width = 250px\n|IATA = WR\n|ICAO = WEN\n|callsign = ENCORE\n|parent = [[WestJet|WestJet Airlines, Ltd.]]\n|founded = {{start date|2013|6|24}}\n|aoc = Canada 17093,<ref>{{TCAOC|2019-08-28|179-03|Westjet+Encore}}</ref> United States 5WJF451F<ref name=\"FAA\">{{Cite web|url=https://av-info.faa.gov/detail.asp?DSGN_CODE=5WJF&OPER_FAR=129&OPER_NAME=WESTJET+ENCORE|title=Federal Aviation Administration - Airline Certificate Information - Detail View|website=av-info.faa.gov|access-date=2019-06-27}}</ref>\n|key_people= Charles Duncan (President, WestJet Encore and Executive Vice President, WestJet Airlines, Ltd.)\n|headquarters = [[Calgary]], [[Alberta]], Canada\n|hubs =\n<div>\n*[[Calgary International Airport|Calgary]]\n*{{nowrap|[[Toronto Pearson International Airport|Toronto\u2013Pearson]]}}\n</div>\n| focus_cities=\n<div>\n*[[Edmonton International Airport|Edmonton]]\n*[[Halifax Stanfield International Airport|Halifax]]\n*[[Vancouver International Airport|Vancouver]]\n</div>|\n|frequent_flyer = WestJet Rewards\n|lounge = \n|alliance = \n|fleet_size = 47<ref name=\"TCFleet\">{{TCregister|WESTJET+ENCORE|Westjet Encore|2018-06-18}}</ref>\n|destinations = 37\n\n|website = [http://www.westjet.com/encore WestJet.com]\n|image=|num_employees=}}\n'''WestJet Encore''' is a Canadian [[regional airline]] that began operations in 2013. It is owned by WestJet Airlines, Ltd. which also is the holding company for [[WestJet Airlines]]. The airline is headquartered in [[Calgary]], [[Alberta]]. In response to internal market studies about future growth limitations by WestJet Airlines operating only [[Boeing 737]] aircraft, WestJet Encore was formed to allow increased frequency of flights by using smaller aircraft, as well as to expand service to routes with less traffic.\n\nThe airline operates [[Bombardier Q400]] NextGen aircraft, a variant of the Bombardier Dash 8. The airline is the fourth largest operator of the [[Bombardier Aerospace|Bombardier]] Q400 series. Pilot bases are in Calgary and [[Toronto]], where many WestJet Encore flights operate. Air service originally started in Western Canada, but routes in the eastern half of the country were added later.\n\nThe airline is a [[low-cost carrier]]. It was initially staffed with non-union employees but the pilots have since unionized. Food is available for purchase. WestJet Encore participates in the WestJet Rewards, a revenue-based frequent flyer program that offers flight discount rewards.\n\n==History==\n===Market conditions leading to the formation of WestJet Encore (2005\u20132013)===\n\nPrior to the formation of WestJet Encore, WestJet Airlines, Inc. internal studies concluded in 2005, when the company had 50 [[Boeing 737]] aircraft, that WestJet would saturate the Canadian commercial airline market when it reached a 90\u2013100 Boeing 737 aircraft fleet. WestJet Airlines had become the second largest airline in Canada in 2002.<ref name=\"2nd largest airline in Canada\">{{cite book|last1=DeWil|first1=Bob|last2=Meyer|first2=Ron|title=Strategy: Process, Content, Context|publisher=Cengage Learning EMEA|isbn=1408019027|page=439}}</ref> Solutions included slowing expansion of the airline or adding smaller aircraft models to serve routes with less traffic. The absence of [[turboprop]] aircraft in the WestJet fleet was seen as a disadvantage compared to competitor [[Air Canada]]. In some cases where Air Canada had smaller aircraft, WestJet either avoided the market or had only one daily flight using a Boeing 737, an aircraft much larger than the ones Air Canada used.<ref name=\"AviationWeekSumers\">{{cite news|last1=Sumers|first1=Brian|title=WestJet Airlines Looks to Expand into Long-Haul|url=http://aviationweek.com/commercial-aviation/westjet-airlines-looks-expand-long-haul|accessdate=18 March 2018|work=Aviation Week and Space Technology}}</ref> Having more flights on a route than a competitor is a competitive advantage.<ref name=\"more flights is an advantage\">{{cite book|last1=Wensveen|first1=John|title=Air Transportation: A Management Advantage|date=2012|publisher=Ashgate Publishing, Ltd.|isbn=1409486826|page=204}}</ref><ref name=\"Global Airline Industry\">{{cite book|last1=Belobaba|first1=Peter|last2=Odoni|first2=Amedeo|last3=Barnhart|first3=Cynthia|title=The Global Airline Industry|date=April 1, 2009|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|isbn=0470744723|page=174|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BRtDl0CJpQIC|accessdate=20 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Westjet Encore Dash-8 Q400.jpg|thumb|alt=WestJet Encore Q400 aircraft with propellers taxing at an airport|WestJet Encore Bombardier Q400 NextGen displaying 2013\u20132015 livery]]\nWestJet made an initial order of 20 Bombardier Dash 8-Q400 NextGen (Q400 NextGen) aircraft through a letter of intent on May 1, 2012, which resulted in a conditional order on June 28, 2012. A firm order of 20 Q400 NextGen and 25 options was announced on August 1, 2012.<ref name=\"BombardierOrder45\">{{cite web|title=WestJet Order for Up to 45 Bombardier Q400 NextGen Aircraft Goes Firm|url=https://www.bombardier.com/en/media/newsList/details.37897-westjet-order-for-up-to-45-bombardier-q400-nextgen-aircraft-goes-firm.bombardiercom.html?|publisher=Bombardier|accessdate=February 4, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209182326/https://www.bombardier.com/en/media/newsList/details.37897-westjet-order-for-up-to-45-bombardier-q400-nextgen-aircraft-goes-firm.bombardiercom.html|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"20 Q400 orders plus 25 options\">{{cite news|last1=Blachly|first1=Linda|title=WestJet firms five more Bombardier Q400 options|url=http://atwonline.com/airframes/westjet-firms-five-more-bombardier-q400-options|accessdate=February 16, 2018|work=Air Transport World|date=July 29, 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180216205907/http://atwonline.com/airframes/westjet-firms-five-more-bombardier-q400-options|archivedate=February 16, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The [[ATR-72|ATR-72-600]] had been considered,<ref>{{cite news|title=WestJet picks Bombardier planes for regional carrier|url=http://ca.reuters.com/article/businessNews/idCABRE84010920120501|accessdate=May 1, 2012|date=May 1, 2012|publisher=Reuters|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120505003813/http://ca.reuters.com/article/businessNews/idCABRE84010920120501|archivedate=May 5, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref> having a lower initial acquisition price and better fuel economy on short flights but slower speed, worse fuel economy on longer flights and slightly less passenger capacity.<ref name=\"GlobeandMailATR72\">{{cite web|title=Bombardier's Q400 faces dogfight for WestJet fleet order|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/report-on-business/bombardiers-q400-faces-dogfight-for-westjet-fleet-order/article4106778/|work=The Globe and Mail|accessdate=February 4, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170129222454/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/report-on-business/bombardiers-q400-faces-dogfight-for-westjet-fleet-order/article4106778/|archivedate=January 29, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"FinancialPostQ400selected\">{{cite web|title=WestJet chooses Bombardier Q400 for regional fleet as earnings soar|url=http://business.financialpost.com/investing/westjet-choses-bombardier-for-regional-fleet-as-earnings-soar|website=Financial Post|accessdate=February 4, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209212159/http://business.financialpost.com/investing/westjet-choses-bombardier-for-regional-fleet-as-earnings-soar|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Inauguration of air service and operating conditions===\n\nThe parent company, WestJet Airlines, Ltd., formed WestJet Encore, a low-cost carrier that is a wholly owned but legally separate airline from WestJet.<ref name=\"Encore is a LCC\">{{cite news|title=Low-cost doesn't necessarily mean best value!|url=http://www.iamaw.ca/low-cost-doesnt-necessarily-mean-best-value/|accessdate=February 10, 2018|publisher=International Association of Machinist and Aerospace Workers|date=April 25, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180211131238/http://www.iamaw.ca/low-cost-doesnt-necessarily-mean-best-value/|archivedate=February 11, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"CAPA profile\">{{cite web|title=WestJet Encore Airline Profile|url=https://centreforaviation.com/data/profiles/airlines/westjet-encore-wr|publisher=CAPA Centre for Aviation|accessdate=February 4, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209122233/https://centreforaviation.com/data/profiles/airlines/westjet-encore-wr|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"WR separate company but pilot track\">{{cite news|last1=Watson|first1=Gary|title=Two companies, one culture|url=https://www.skiesmag.com/news/18312-two-companies-one-culture-html/|accessdate=February 16, 2018|publisher=Skies|date=February 23, 2013|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180216144026/https://www.skiesmag.com/news/18312-two-companies-one-culture-html/|archivedate=February 16, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Prior to the selection of the Encore name, other names were considered, including [[Chinook wind|Chinook]], Echo, and Reach.<ref name=\"Echo Reach Chinook\">{{cite news|last1=Deveau|first1=Scott|title=WestJet trademarks potential names for regional carrier|url=http://business.financialpost.com/transportation/westjet-trademarks-potential-names-for-regional-carrier|accessdate=February 9, 2018|work=Financial Post|date=September 12, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209213705/http://business.financialpost.com/transportation/westjet-trademarks-potential-names-for-regional-carrier|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Calgary was selected for the WestJet Encore corporate headquarters but Toronto Pearson International Airport was also considered.<ref name=\"YYZ rejected as HQ\">{{cite news|last1=Osbourn|first1=Erin|title=WestJet passes on Pearson, makes Calgary new regional HQ|url=https://www.mississauga.com/news-story/4242402-westjet-passes-on-pearson-makes-calgary-new-regional-hq/|accessdate=February 10, 2018|work=Mississauga News|date=October 31, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180211072205/https://www.mississauga.com/news-story/4242402-westjet-passes-on-pearson-makes-calgary-new-regional-hq/|archivedate=February 11, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> WestJet Encore received an Air Operator Certificate separate from WestJet Airlines on June 12, 2013.<ref name=\"WR AOC\">{{cite web|title=WestJet Encore receives its Air Operator Certificate|url=https://worldairlinenews.com/2013/06/12/westjet-encore-receives-its-air-operator-certificate/|website=World Airline News|accessdate=February 3, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180129141030/https://worldairlinenews.com/2013/06/12/westjet-encore-receives-its-air-operator-certificate/|archivedate=January 29, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"ATW AOC\">{{cite web|last1=Karp|first1=Aaron|title=WestJet Encore receives AOC from Transport Canada|url=http://atwonline.com/finance-amp-data/westjet-encore-receives-aoc-transport-canada|website=Air Transport World|accessdate=February 4, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209125226/http://atwonline.com/finance-amp-data/westjet-encore-receives-aoc-transport-canada|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn June 24, 2013, with two Q400s in its fleet, it began flights.<ref name=\"AirlineReporterInguralFlt\">{{cite web|last1=Slutsken|first1=Howard|title=WestJet Encore Celebrates Inaugural Q400 Flight from Calgary|url=https://www.airlinereporter.com/2013/06/westjet-encore-launch-day/|website=Airline Reporter|accessdate=February 4, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170702085317/http://www.airlinereporter.com/2013/06/westjet-encore-launch-day/|archivedate=July 2, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> That day, the airline flew between [[Calgary International Airport]] and [[Saskatoon John G. Diefenbaker International Airport|Saskatoon]], [[Nanaimo Airport|Nanaimo (British Columbia)]], and [[Fort St. John Airport|Fort St. John (British Columbia)]] as well as between Fort. St. John and [[Vancouver International Airport|Vancouver]].<ref name=\"Encore starts\">{{cite web|title=WestJet Encore celebrates three years: WestJet's regional airline now at 32 destinations and 30 aircraft|url=https://www.newswire.ca/news-releases/westjet-encore-celebrates-three-years-584242681.html|publisher=Cision|accessdate=January 30, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210002159/https://www.newswire.ca/news-releases/westjet-encore-celebrates-three-years-584242681.html|archivedate=February 10, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The IATA assigned WestJet Encore an airline code of \"WR\",<ref name=\"EncoreisWR\">{{cite web|title=WestJet Encore C-GWEN|url=http://www.airfleets.net/ficheapp/plane-dh8-4537.htm|publisher=Airfleets.net|accessdate=February 5, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209182341/http://www.airfleets.net/ficheapp/plane-dh8-4537.htm|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> which had previously been used by [[Royal Tongan Airlines]].<ref name=\"Royal Tongan\">{{cite web|last1=van Noordenne|first1=Marcel|title=Royal Tongan Airlines|url=http://www.b757.info/royal-tongan-airlines/|publisher=MNVS Boeing 757|accessdate=February 5, 2018|ref=December 7, 2014}}</ref>\n\nSome WestJet Encore flights were new routes not served by the WestJet mainline carrier because there was insufficient traffic to support Boeing 737 flights. Other WestJet Encore flights increased frequencies on existing WestJet routes.<ref name=AviationWeekSumers /> WestJet Encore's service was initially limited to Western Canada, but it opened service in the eastern part of the country<!--not Eastern Canada, as NB is Eastern Canada, not Toronto--> in June 2014 with a route from Toronto to Thunder Bay, Ontario.<ref name=\"WRexpandsEast\">{{cite web|last1=Stephenson|first1=Amanda|title=WestJet Encore begins march east|url=https://calgaryherald.com/business/westjet+encore+begins+march+east/9974530/story.html| work=Calgary Herald|accessdate=February 5, 2018|ref=June 25, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140715051140/http://www.calgaryherald.com/business/WestJet+Encore+begins+march+east/9974530/story.html |archivedate=July 15, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref> It later began service on eastern routes centred on Toronto and Halifax.<ref name = \"WRexpandsEast\" /> WestJet Encore moved into the international market in 2016, with flights serving [[Boston Logan Airport]];<ref name=\"BOS service\">{{cite web|title=WestJet Encore inaugurates service to Boston|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/westjet-encore-inaugurates-service-to-boston-572079671.html|publisher=Cision|accessdate=February 5, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210002146/https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/westjet-encore-inaugurates-service-to-boston-572079671.html|archivedate=February 10, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Boston first Intl\">{{cite news|last1=Lu|first1=Vanessa|title=WestJet to launch regional Toronto-Boston service|url=https://www.thestar.com/business/2015/07/20/westjet-to-launch-regional-toronto-boston-service.html|accessdate=February 16, 2018|work=Toronto Star|date=July 20, 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180216143959/https://www.thestar.com/business/2015/07/20/westjet-to-launch-regional-toronto-boston-service.html|archivedate=February 16, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> [[Nashville International Airport]] was added the following year.<ref name=\"BNA service\">{{cite web|title=WestJet Launches Calgary's First Nonstop to Nashville|url=http://press.tnvacation.com/news-archive/westjet-launches-calgarys-first-nonstop-nashville|publisher=Tennessee Department of Tourist Development|accessdate=February 5, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210002141/http://press.tnvacation.com/news-archive/westjet-launches-calgarys-first-nonstop-nashville|archivedate=February 10, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[File:WestJetQ400C-GEWRUnloadingYYJAugust2018.jpg|thumb|left|A WestJet Encore Bombardier Q400 displaying the new livery]]\nWestJet Encore flies Q400 NextGen on regional flights up to 700 nautical miles.<ref name=\"Q400 700nmi flights\">{{cite web|title=Flight Review of WestJet Encore: On Board Their Newest Q400|url=https://www.wingborn.com/flight-review-of-westjet-encore-on-board-their-newest-q400/|publisher=Wingborn|accessdate=February 5, 2018|ref=October 25, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209183808/https://www.wingborn.com/flight-review-of-westjet-encore-on-board-their-newest-q400/|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> 50% of WestJet Encore passengers are traveling on connecting flights with WestJet.<ref name=\"WRexpandsEast\" /><ref name=\"YYC ltd flexible gates\"/> The WestJet Encore fleet of Q400s expanded to 18 aircraft by March 2015, and later to 34 aircraft by December 2016 and to 43 aircraft by December 2017.<ref name=AviationWeekSumers/><ref name=\"Utah Herald 34 Q400s\">{{cite news|last1=Roges|first1=Linda|title=ProPetro Holding Corp. (PUMP Reaches $17.65 After 6.00% Down Move; Westjet Airlines Ltd (WJAFF) Shorts Decreased By 17.24%|url=https://utahherald.com/propetro-holding-corp-pump-reaches-17-65-after-6-00-down-move-westjet-airlines-ltd-wjaff-shorts-decreased-by-17-24/|accessdate=February 5, 2018|work=Utah Herald|date=February 4, 2018}}{{Dead link|date=August 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> In 2015, WestJet Encore was the fastest-growing operator of Q400 aircraft.<ref name=\"Encore starts\" /> By 2017, it was the fourth largest operator of Q400 aircraft in the world.<ref name=\"WR YUL BOS 4th largest Q400\">{{cite news|last1=Simpson|first1=Brian|title=WestJet Launches Montreal-Boston Service|url=https://ca.travelpulse.com/news/airlines/westjet-launches-montreal-boston-service.html|accessdate=February 5, 2018|publisher=Travel Pulse Canada|date=October 15, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209122235/https://ca.travelpulse.com/news/airlines/westjet-launches-montreal-boston-service.html|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2015, WestJet Encore adopted a revised livery. The tail and type style used with the word \"WestJet\" remained the same, but the teal-and-blue geometric widget ahead of the WestJet titles was replaced with a teal-and-blue stylized maple leaf with a similar pattern.<ref name=\"revised livery\">{{cite news|title=WestJet Gets a New Logo&nbsp;\u2013 Really!|url=http://www.wingborn.com/westjet-gets-a-new-logo-really/|accessdate=February 8, 2018|publisher=Wingborn/Airline Reporter|date=August 27, 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209183813/http://www.wingborn.com/westjet-gets-a-new-logo-really/|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Q400 new livery\">{{cite web|last1=Flynn|first1=Shawn|title=WestJet Encore de Havilland Canada DHC-8-400Q / Bombardier Q400 C-GKWE|url=https://www.airplane-pictures.net/photo/903207/c-gkwe-westjet-encore-de-havilland-canada-dhc-8-400q-bombardier-q400/|publisher=Airplane Pictures|accessdate=February 8, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210002131/https://www.airplane-pictures.net/photo/903207/c-gkwe-westjet-encore-de-havilland-canada-dhc-8-400q-bombardier-q400/|archivedate=February 10, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[File:WestJet Encore - Bombardier Dash 8 Q400 (Quintin Soloviev).png|thumb|WestJet Encore Bombardier Dash 8-Q400 at Qu\u00e9bec City Jean Lesage International Airport.]]\n\nWestjet Encore has a partially unionized workforce. Initially having an entirely non-union staff, the airline became a target for union drives starting in 2014.<ref name = \"WestJet Encore pilots unionize\">{{cite news|title=WestJet Encore pilots unionize and flight attendants could be next|url=https://ca.finance.yahoo.com/news/westjet-encore-pilots-unionize-flight-194612798.html|accessdate=February 6, 2018|publisher=Yahoo Finance Canada|date=November 1, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209122406/https://ca.finance.yahoo.com/news/westjet-encore-pilots-unionize-flight-194612798.html|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Starting January 1, 2016, the airline management initiated WestJet Pilots Association, a subgroup of the WestJet Proactive Management Team, to ratify pilot contracts between with WestJet Encore.<ref name=\"WJPA before ALPA\">{{cite news|title=WestJet Encore Pilots Ratify Deal|url=http://www.cbj.ca/westjet-encore-pilots-ratify-new-contract/|accessdate=February 6, 2018|work=Canadian Business Journal|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210002228/http://www.cbj.ca/westjet-encore-pilots-ratify-new-contract/|archivedate=February 10, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The pilots union which represents many pilots that fly for U.S. carriers,<ref name=\"ALPA 59000 pilots in US Canada\">{{cite web|title=What We Do&nbsp;\u2013 ALPA|url=http://www.alpa.org/en/about-alpa/what-we-do|publisher=Air Line Pilots Association|accessdate=February 6, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170606122948/http://www.alpa.org/en/about-alpa/what-we-do|archivedate=June 6, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> the [[Air Line Pilots Association]], was successful in unionizing the 500-pilot workforce in November 2017.<ref name=\"500 pilots join ALPA union\">{{cite news|title=WestJet's 500 Encore pilots officially join union; company 'disappointed'|url=https://calgaryherald.com/business/local-business/westjets-500-encore-pilots-officially-join-union-company-disappointed|accessdate=February 6, 2018|work=Calgary Herald|date=November 30, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201025411/http://calgaryherald.com/business/local-business/westjets-500-encore-pilots-officially-join-union-company-disappointed|archivedate=December 1, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Pilot bases are located in Calgary and Toronto. WestJet pilots are required to be Canadian citizens or Canadian permanent residents.<ref name=\"PilotCareerCentre\">{{cite web|title=WestJet Encore|url=https://www.pilotcareercentre.com/Air-Carrier-PCC-Profile/3363/WestJet-Encore|publisher=Pilot Career Centre Global|accessdate=February 4, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209182321/https://www.pilotcareercentre.com/Air-Carrier-PCC-Profile/3363/WestJet-Encore|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Pilot shortages in the airline industry have affected WestJet Encore, resulting in requirements that newly hired pilots need only 1,000 flight hours of experience prior to hiring.<ref name=\"pilot shortage\">{{cite news|last1=Donnelly|first1=Sara|title=Pilot shortage affects airline|url=http://www.prpeak.com/business/pilot-shortage-affects-airline-1.23153044|accessdate=February 1, 2018|work=Powell River Peak|date=January 24, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180124220316/http://www.prpeak.com/business/pilot-shortage-affects-airline-1.23153044|archivedate=January 24, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Pilots are guaranteed an eventual higher paying position flying larger jets at WestJet, unlike competitor airline [[Jazz (airline)|Jazz]], which does not offer guarantees of an eventual job at Air Canada.<ref name=\"WR separate company but pilot track\" /> WestJet Encore and its flight attendants reached an agreement regarding compensation and work rules beginning January 1, 2018, for a one-year period. However, the Canadian Union of Public Employees (CUPE), who was not a party to the agreement, announced that it would continue efforts to unionize the flight attendant ranks.<ref name=\"CUPE flight attendants 2018\">{{cite news|title=Union drive still on after WestJet Encore flight attendant agreement: CUPE|url=http://business.financialpost.com/pmn/business-pmn/westjet-encore-reaches-peace-with-flight-attendants-months-after-union-drive|accessdate=February 6, 2018|work=Financial Post|date=January 9, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209190302/http://business.financialpost.com/pmn/business-pmn/westjet-encore-reaches-peace-with-flight-attendants-months-after-union-drive|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn October 31, 2016, a $2 billion, two million square foot international terminal for U.S. cross border and international flights opened at Calgary International Airport, the largest hub of WestJet Encore and its affiliate WestJet.<ref name=\"Calg Herald 20Dec16 YYC walk baggage 2M sq ft\">{{cite news|last1=Stephenson|first1=Amanda|title=WestJet CEO blasts new terminal at YYC, says airport authority hasn't listened to concerns|url=https://calgaryherald.com/business/local-business/westjet-ceo-blasts-new-terminal-at-yyc-says-airport-authority-hasnt-listened-to-concerns|accessdate=February 6, 2018|work=Calgary Herald|date=December 20, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170708164910/http://calgaryherald.com/business/local-business/westjet-ceo-blasts-new-terminal-at-yyc-says-airport-authority-hasnt-listened-to-concerns|archivedate=July 8, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"YYC largest hub\">{{cite news|last1=Rumbolt|first1=Ryan|title=WestJet adds dozens of Calgary departures as economy shows signs of recovery|url=https://calgaryherald.com/news/local-news/westjet-adds-dozens-of-calgary-departures-as-economy-shows-signs-of-recovery|accessdate=14 March 2018|work=Calgary Herald|date=January 29, 2018}}</ref> Despite consultation with the airlines, the terminal design proved problematic.<ref name=\"Airlines consulted for YYC\">{{cite news|last1=Tighe|first1=Tony|title=WestJet says passengers upset with Calgary airport connection travel times|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/3142232/westjet-says-passengers-upset-with-calgary-airport-connection-travel-times/|accessdate=14 March 2018|publisher=Global News|date=December 31, 2016}}</ref> The Calgary Airport Authority CEO characterized the new terminal as being \"long on aesthetics and short on functionality.\"<ref name=\"YYC CEO on Intl Term\">{{cite news|last1=Yedlin|first1=Deborah|title=Yedlin: New CEO determined to fix international terminal troubles at YYC|url=https://calgaryherald.com/business/local-business/yedlin-new-ceo-determined-to-fix-international-terminal-troubles-at-yyc|accessdate=February 6, 2018|work=Calgary Herald|date=February 28, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170609141047/http://calgaryherald.com/business/local-business/yedlin-new-ceo-determined-to-fix-international-terminal-troubles-at-yyc|archivedate=June 9, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> There is reduced aircraft efficiency due to the need to tow aircraft to another concourse if an aircraft is used for both domestic and either U.S. cross border or international flights<ref name=\"YYC ltd flexible gates\">{{cite news|last1=Yedlin|first1=Deborah|title=Yedlin: New international terminal at YYC falls short of its peers|url=https://calgaryherald.com/business/energy/yedlin-new-international-terminal-at-yyc-falls-short-of-its-peers|accessdate=February 6, 2018|work=Calgary Herald|date=January 11, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170115055230/http://calgaryherald.com/business/energy/yedlin-new-international-terminal-at-yyc-falls-short-of-its-peers|archivedate=January 15, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> as well as the need to hire additional staff because they cannot be deployed to more than one concourse due to long walking distances.<ref name=\"CBC YYC terminal doesnt work\">{{cite news|last1=Bell|first1=David|title='It just doesn't work for us': WestJet on new YYC international terminal|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/calgary/westjet-yyc-terminal-complaints-1.3908218|accessdate=February 6, 2018|publisher=CBC|date=December 21, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171221090816/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/calgary/westjet-yyc-terminal-complaints-1.3908218|archivedate=December 21, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The baggage system of the new terminal is inoperable with the rest of the airport from 2016 to 2019.<ref name=\"Calg Herald 20Dec16 YYC walk baggage 2M sq ft\"/> Passenger problems include WestJet trans-border and international gates being up to a two-kilometre walk to the domestic WestJet gates as well as lack of enough seating at the gate so passengers sit on the floor.<ref name=\"Calg Herald 20Dec16 YYC walk baggage 2M sq ft\"/><ref name=\"YYC CEO on Intl Term\"/><ref name=\"CBC YYC terminal doesnt work\"/> These problems are seen as a threat to passenger traffic, which might be driven to other connecting airports, such as Seattle or Vancouver, cities that WestJet Encore has fewer or no flights serving.<ref name=\"YYC ltd flexible gates\"/>\n\n==Corporate affairs==\n===Management===\n\nWestJet Encore is a wholly owned company of WestJet Airlines, Ltd. Sales and marketing of WestJet Encore flights are conducted by WestJet, An Alberta Partnership, which is jointly owned by two corporate entities owned by WestJet Airlines, Ltd.<ref name=\"2016 annual report\">{{cite web|last1=WestJet Airlines, Ltd.|title=2016 Annual Information Form|url=https://www.westjet.com/assets/wj-web/documents/en/about-us/financialReports/WestJet2016AIF.pdf|publisher=WestJet|accessdate=14 March 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe first president of WestJet Encore was Ferio Pugliese, who retained his title of Executive Vice President at WestJet Airlines, Ltd. He was hired in November 2012 coming from WestJet, where he began work in 2007.<ref name=\"Puegliese hired\">{{cite web|title=WestJet appoints President, WestJet Encore|url=http://westjet2.mediaroom.com/index.php?item=719&s=43|publisher=WestJet|accessdate=February 8, 2018}}</ref> He left<ref name=\"Bloomberg about Ferio\">{{cite web|title=Ferio Pugliese|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/profiles/people/7339778-ferio-pugliese|publisher=Bloomberg|accessdate=6 April 2018}}</ref> in 2016 to become an Executive Vice President at [[Hydro One|Hydro One Ltd.]], an electricity company.<ref name=\"Pugliese Hydro One\">{{cite news|title=westjet airlines ltd (WJAFF:OTC US)|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=25985084&privcapId=883197|accessdate=February 8, 2018|publisher=Bloomberg}}</ref> He was replaced in September 2016 by Charles Duncan, an American who previously worked as Senior Vice President of Technical Operations at [[United Airlines]] and, earlier in his career, was Chief Operating Officer at [[Continental Micronesia]].<ref name=\"Charles Duncan President\">{{cite web|title=WestJet announces new president for WestJet Encore|url=https://www.newswire.ca/news-releases/westjet-announces-new-president-for-westjet-encore-624644754.html|publisher=Cision|accessdate=February 8, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170611075237/http://www.newswire.ca/news-releases/westjet-announces-new-president-for-westjet-encore-624644754.html|archivedate=June 11, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Financials===\n\nFinancial statistics are not released separately for WestJet Encore but reported for WestJet Airlines, Ltd., which comprises several units and the larger WestJet Airlines.<ref name=\"Annual report\">{{cite web|title=2016 Annual Report|url=https://www.westjet.com/assets/wj-web/documents/en/about-us/financialReports/WestJet2016AR.pdf|publisher=WestJet|accessdate=February 9, 2018}}</ref> WestJet Encore has increased traffic in markets that it served as well as lowered airfares 30\u201340% than was previously available.<ref name=\"WR increase traffic lowers fares\">{{cite news|title=WestJet after 20 years. The new LCC challenges: preserving the culture but rising to the business|url=https://centreforaviation.com/insights/analysis/westjet-turns-20-the-new-lcc-challenges-preserving-the-culture-but-rising-to-the-business-280095|accessdate=February 10, 2018|publisher=CAPA Centre for Aviation|date=May 9, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180211131158/https://centreforaviation.com/insights/analysis/westjet-turns-20-the-new-lcc-challenges-preserving-the-culture-but-rising-to-the-business-280095|archivedate=February 11, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Destinations==\n{{Further|List of WestJet destinations}}\n{{Location map+ | Canada\n| AlternativeMap = Relief map of Canada.png\n| width   = 250\n| caption = Airports served by scheduled WestJet Encore flights in January 2018 (two additional United States airports not shown, Nashville and Myrtle Beach)\n| places  =\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 45.42\n  | lon_deg = -75.7\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 49.25\n  | lon_deg = -123.1\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 51\n  | lon_deg = -114\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 53.5\n  | lon_deg = -113.5\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 56.7\n  | lon_deg = -111.3\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 55.2\n  | lon_deg = -118.7\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 49\n  | lon_deg = -122.3\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 49.7\n  | lon_deg = -124.9\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 56.2\n  | lon_deg = -120.85\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 50.6\n  | lon_deg = -120.3\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 49.9\n  | lon_deg = -119.5\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 49.15\n  | lon_deg = -123.9\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 49.5\n  | lon_deg = -119.6\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 53.9\n  | lon_deg = -122.74\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 54.5\n  | lon_deg = -128.6\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 48.4\n  | lon_deg = -123.35\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 49.9\n  | lon_deg = -99.95\n  | label   = \n  }}\n <!-- {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 36.2\n  | lon_deg = -86.8\n  | label   = \n  }} -->\n<!--  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 33.75\n  | lon_deg = -78.9\n  | label   = \n  }} -->\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 49.9\n  | lon_deg = -97.1\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 45.95\n  | lon_deg = -66.66\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 46.1\n  | lon_deg = -64.8\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 47.6\n  | lon_deg = -52.7\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 48.9\n  | lon_deg = -54.5\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 49.2\n  | lon_deg = -57.4\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 46.1\n  | lon_deg = -61.0\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 44.9\n  | lon_deg = -63.5\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 62.5\n  | lon_deg = -114.4\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 45.5\n  | lon_deg = -73.7\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 46.8\n  | lon_deg = -71.4\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 52.2\n  | lon_deg = -106.7\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 50.4\n  | lon_deg = -104.65\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 46.6\n  | lon_deg = -80.8\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 48.3\n  | lon_deg = -89.3\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 43.65\n  | lon_deg = -79.6\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 43\n  | lon_deg = -81.15\n  | label   = \n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | Canada\n  | lat_deg = 42.35\n  | lon_deg = -71\n  | label   = \n  }}\n}}\n\nWestJet Encore flies regional routes throughout Canada, primarily to or from Calgary, Toronto, and Halifax. Routes include smaller cities, such as [[Brandon, Manitoba]] to Calgary, two cities with an oil industry. This new service re-introduced air service to Brandon.<ref name=\"Brandon and oil industry\">{{cite news|last1=Forlanski|first1=Tamara|title=WestJet lands in Brandon with service to Calgary|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/557244/brandon-gets-westjet-service-starting-sept-3/|accessdate=February 9, 2018|publisher=Global News|date=May 13, 2013|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209122844/https://globalnews.ca/news/557244/brandon-gets-westjet-service-starting-sept-3/|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Other routes are increased frequencies on existing WestJet routes, such as between Calgary and Saskatoon.<ref name=\"Saskatoon schedule\">{{cite news|last1=Streck|first1=Aaron|title=WestJet Encore touches down in Saskatoon|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/671271/westjet-encore-touches-down-in-saskatoon/|accessdate=February 9, 2018|publisher=Global News|date=June 25, 2013|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209122839/https://globalnews.ca/news/671271/westjet-encore-touches-down-in-saskatoon/|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> WestJet Encore services four destinations outside of Canada, namely Boston, Nashville, Portland, OR and on a seasonal basis, [[Myrtle Beach International Airport|Myrtle Beach, South Carolina]].<ref name=\"MYR SC\">{{cite news|last1=McGee|first1=Kendell|title=Airlines announce more direct flights, lower fares in and out of MYR|url=http://www.wbtw.com/news/airlines-announce-more-direct-flights-lower-fares-in-and-out-of-myr/868551671|accessdate=10 April 2018|publisher=WBTV|date=January 19, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"BOS service and BNA\">{{cite web|title=WestJet Encore inaugurates service to Boston|url=https://www.meetingscanada.com/boston-toronto-westjet-encore-service/|publisher=Meetings Canada|accessdate=February 5, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209182156/https://www.meetingscanada.com/boston-toronto-westjet-encore-service/|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> WestJet Encore operated flights between [[Kelowna International Airport|Kelowna, British Columbia]] and [[Fort McMurray International Airport|Fort McMurray, Alberta]], neither a WestJet Encore hub airport, from 2014 to 2016 but discontinued flights amid a decline in the oil industry due to lower oil prices.<ref name=\"YLW YMM service begins\">{{cite web|title=WestJet Encore launches new Fort McMurray service|url=https://ylw.kelowna.ca/news-events/news/westjet-encore-launches-new-fort-mcmurray-service|publisher=Kelowna International Airport|accessdate=8 April 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"YMM YLW service ending\">{{cite news|title=WestJet suspends Fort McMurray to Kelowna service amid oil slump|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/calgary/westjet-suspends-flights-fort-mcmurray-kelowna-1.3410240|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=CBC|date=January 19, 2016}}</ref> WestJet Encore flights are numbered as flight 3100 to 3899.<ref name=\"flights 3100 3899\">{{cite web|title=WestJet Encore|url=https://www.westjet.com/en-ca/about-us/fleet/westjet-encore|publisher=WestJet|accessdate=February 9, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210002347/https://www.westjet.com/en-ca/about-us/fleet/westjet-encore|archivedate=February 10, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Fleet==\n[[File:C-FWEP Westjet Encore Dash 8-Q400.jpg|thumb|left|alt=WestJet Encore Q400 in flight with propellers turning and landing gear extended|WestJet Encore Bombardier Q400 NextGen with landing gear extended]]\n\nWestJet Encore operates one type of aircraft, the Bombardier Q400 NextGen, an updated version of the Q400 with updated landing gear, redesigned interiors, lighting, and larger overhead cabin storage. In turn, the Q400 is an updated version of the Bombardier Dash 8-400 that has active noise suppression to create a quieter passenger cabin. To prevent freezing of water lines during overnight stays at airports with cold weather, the airline rendered the water flow to the lavatory basins inoperative in 2013.<ref name=\"WR Q400 review\">{{cite news|last1=Slutsken|first1=Howard|title=Flight Review of Westjet Encore: On Board Their Newest Q400|url=https://www.airlinereporter.com/2013/10/flight-review-of-westjet-encore-on-board-their-newest-q400/|accessdate=January 30, 2018|publisher=Airline Reporter|date=October 25, 2013|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170829081507/http://www.airlinereporter.com/2013/10/flight-review-of-westjet-encore-on-board-their-newest-q400/|archivedate=August 29, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nWestJet Encore uses a navAero supplied Windows-OS based [[electronic flight bag]] (EFB) that can connect to the aircraft. In conjunction with a WestJet developed Integrated Communication and Application System (ICAS), objective flight data can be shared with maintenance personnel improving aircraft efficiency. One example of use would be after an aircraft was subjected to severe turbulence, EFB and ICAS could determine whether or not objective thresholds were exceeded. If such thresholds are not exceeded, four hours of maintenance and inspection are avoided instead of having pilots subjectively characterize the level of turbulence.<ref name=\"MRO\">{{cite web |title=Exploiting Turboprop Data For Smarter Maintenance |url=http://www.mro-network.com/maintenance-repair-overhaul/exploiting-turboprop-data-smarter-maintenance |publisher=MRO Network |date=August 21, 2017 |accessdate=January 2, 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180103133306/http://www.mro-network.com/maintenance-repair-overhaul/exploiting-turboprop-data-smarter-maintenance |archivedate=January 3, 2018 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nAs of August 2019, the WestJet Encore fleet consists of the following aircraft:<ref>{{cite journal |title=Global Airline Guide 2019 (Part One) |journal=Airliner World |volume=October 2019 |page=9}}</ref><ref>https://www.westjet.com/en-ca/about-us/fleet/westjet-encore</ref>\n<center>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; margin:0.5em\"\n|+ WestJet Encore fleet'''\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:120px;\" |Aircraft\n! rowspan=\"2\" |In service\n! colspan=\"3\" | Passengers\n|-\n! <abbr title=\"Premium Economy\">W</abbr>\n! <abbr title=\"Economy\">Y</abbr>\n! Total\n|-\n|[[De Havilland Canada Dash 8#Series 400|Bombardier Q400]]\n|47\n|10\n|68\n|78\n|-\n|}\n</center>\n\n==Marketing==\nWestJet Encore participates in WestJet Rewards, a [[frequent flyer program]] and loyalty scheme originally started by WestJet. Instead of miles or points, WestJet Dollars are earned by participants and can be redeemed as full or partial payment of future airfare. Participants earn 1% of their airfare in WestJet Dollars. Elite level participants, who spend $3000 or more per year in WestJet airfare are classified as Silver or Gold and earn a 3% or 5% rate in WestJet Dollars.<ref name=\"WestJet Rewards Tiers\">{{cite web|title=Tiers|url=https://www.westjet.com/en-ca/rewards/tiers/index|publisher=WestJet|accessdate=February 9, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210002344/https://www.westjet.com/en-ca/rewards/tiers/index|archivedate=February 10, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> WestJet also participates in WestJet Rewards as does Air France (2017\u2013present),<ref name=\"Flying Blue\">{{cite news|title=Air France-KLM and WestJet now offer reciprocal frequent flyer benefits|url=http://www.travelweek.ca/news/air-france-klm-westjet-now-offer-reciprocal-frequent-flyer-benefits/|accessdate=February 10, 2018|publisher=Travel Week|date=August 30, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210121008/http://www.travelweek.ca/news/air-france-klm-westjet-now-offer-reciprocal-frequent-flyer-benefits/|archivedate=February 10, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> KLM (2017\u2013present),<ref name=\"Flying Blue\"/> Delta Airlines (2014\u2013present),<ref name=\"Delta Skymiles\">{{cite news|title=Delta and WestJet Start New Accrual Partnership|url=https://pro.delta.com/content/agency/mx/en/news/products---services-archive/2014/december-2014/delta-and-westjet-start-new-accrual-partnership-.html|accessdate=February 10, 2018|publisher=Delta Airlines|date=December 18, 2014}}</ref> and Qantas (2016\u2013present).<ref name=\"Qantas Frequent Flyer\">{{cite news|title=WestJet, Qantas unveil reciprocal frequent flyer agreement: expands on existing code-share relationship|url=https://www.qantasnewsroom.com.au/media-releases/westjet-qantas-unveil-reciprocal-frequent-flyer-agreement-expands-on-existing-code-share-relationship/|accessdate=February 10, 2018|publisher=Qantas Airways|date=May 26, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210235026/https://www.qantasnewsroom.com.au/media-releases/westjet-qantas-unveil-reciprocal-frequent-flyer-agreement-expands-on-existing-code-share-relationship/|archivedate=February 10, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> WestJet Dollars earned as a base amount do not expire but bonus amounts have an expiry date.<ref name=\"WS Rewards terms and conditions\">{{cite web|title=Terms and conditions \u2013 WestJet Rewards|url=https://www.westjet.com/en-ca/rewards/terms-conditions|publisher=WestJet|accessdate=February 9, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210002342/https://www.westjet.com/en-ca/rewards/terms-conditions|archivedate=February 10, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nPassengers flying on WestJet Encore may alternatively receive credit in Air France/KLM Flying Blue,<ref name=\"Flying Blue2\">{{cite web|title=Westjet|url=https://www.flyingblue.com/earn-miles/airlines/partner/288/westjet.html|publisher=Flying Blue|accessdate=February 9, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209122217/https://www.flyingblue.com/earn-miles/airlines/partner/288/westjet.html|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Flying Blue CTV News\">{{cite news|last1=Franklin|first1=Michael|title=WestJet, Air France and KLM announce frequent flyer redemption agreement|url=https://calgary.ctvnews.ca/westjet-air-france-and-klm-announce-frequent-flyer-redemption-agreement-1.3678758|accessdate=February 16, 2018|publisher=CTV Calgary|date=November 15, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180216204353/https://calgary.ctvnews.ca/westjet-air-france-and-klm-announce-frequent-flyer-redemption-agreement-1.3678758|archivedate=February 16, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Delta Skymiles,<ref name=\"Delta Skymiles2\">{{cite web|title=How to earn miles|url=https://www.delta.com/content/www/en_US/skymiles/how-to-earn-miles/airline-partners.html|publisher=Delta Airlines|accessdate=February 9, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210002239/https://www.delta.com/content/www/en_US/skymiles/how-to-earn-miles/airline-partners.html|archivedate=February 10, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> or Qantas Frequent Flyer<ref name=\"Qantas Frequent Flyer2\">{{cite web|title=Airline Partners \u2013 Westjet|url=https://www.qantas.com/fflyer/dyn/partners/airline/westjet|publisher=Qantas Airways|accessdate=February 9, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209182326/https://www.qantas.com/fflyer/dyn/partners/airline/westjet|archivedate=February 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Cabins and services==\n[[File:WestJetEncoreQ400SeatOverviewAugust2018.webm|thumb|Seat tour of a WestJet Encore Bombardier Q400 aircraft]]\nAs well as economy class seating, WestJet Encore aircraft has a designated Plus section. Unlike the Plus section on the mainline carrier, WestJet, it does not have increased legroom. The Plus section on WestJet Encore has seating in the forward part of the cabin and does not have change fees when changing flights ticketed.<ref name=\"Plus section\">{{cite web|title=Plus Upgrade|url=https://www.westjet.com/en-ca/travel-info/check-in/options/plus-upgrade|website=WestJet|accessdate=February 10, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180211071541/https://www.westjet.com/en-ca/travel-info/check-in/options/plus-upgrade|archivedate=February 11, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The majority of WestJet Encore flights do not use [[jet bridge]]s and are instead ground loaded, meaning the passengers exit the terminal onto the [[Airport apron|apron]] before stepping on to the aircraft. WestJet Encore aircraft do not have drop down oxygen masks, which are not required by regulations due to the aircraft's certification to operate up to 25,000 feet in altitude.<ref name=\"smoke in cabin\">{{cite news|title=TSB investigators sent to B.C. airport after smoke-filled WestJet flight's emergency landing|url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/tsb-investigators-sent-to-b-c-airport-after-smoke-filled-westjet-flight-s-emergency-landing-1.3851949|accessdate=22 March 2018|publisher=CTV News}}</ref>\n\nStarting in 2014, newly hired flight attendants are required to be bilingual in English and French. As a result, 94% of flight attendants are bilingual.<ref name=\"CBC bilingual flight attendants\">{{cite news|last1=Marowitz|first1=Ross|title=WestJet takes on Air Canada on its home turf by adding service in Quebec|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/business/westjet-quebec-expansion-1.3980761|accessdate=January 30, 2018|publisher=CBC|date=February 13, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171102150710/http://www.cbc.ca/news/business/westjet-quebec-expansion-1.3980761|archivedate=November 2, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nFood is available for purchase.\n\nWestJet Encore does not operate airport lounges but has arrangements with private, non-airline affiliated airport lounges where WestJet Encore passengers are extended a discount for pay-for-visit use.<ref name=\"airport lounges\">{{cite web|title=Airport Lounges|url=https://www.westjet.com/en-ca/book-trip/business-travel/airport-lounges|publisher=WestJet|accessdate=February 10, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170815235432/https://www.westjet.com/en-ca/book-trip/business-travel/airport-lounges|archivedate=August 15, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[WestJet Link]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{commons category|WestJet Encore}}\n{{Portal bar|Canada|Companies|Aviation}}\n\n{{Airlines of Canada}}\n\n[[Category:Air Transport Association of Canada]]\n[[Category:WestJet]]\n[[Category:Low-cost carriers]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Calgary]]\n[[Category:Canadian brands]]\n[[Category:Regional airline brands]]\n[[Category:Airlines established in 2013]]\n", "name_user": "John of Reading", "label": "safe", "comment": "Typo fixing, replaced: taxing \u2192 taxiing", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WestJet_Encore"}
